main event: A single unidentified object was observed traveling in a straight line over Dahlgren, Virginia.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on January 3, 1953, at 2215Z., The object resembled a shooting star and disappeared within 62 seconds., No sound or trail was reported during the observation., The duration of the sighting was approximately 1 minute., The report was documented under Project Blue Book.
witness description: Civilian and Military sources reported the sighting.
